         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Kew March 19/64. ¶ My dear Dr Mueller ¶  ¶ I am still very busy with the New Zealand Manual, of which 190 pages are in the press, &amp; I hope to publish Part I Phaenogameae, in the course of a month or s...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">64.03.19b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS black-edged; Hooker's daughter Maria had died on 28 September 1863.</p>
               </note>Kew March 19/64.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Dr Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am still very busy with the New Zealand Manual, of which 190 pages are in the press, &amp; I hope to publish Part I Phaenogameae, in the course of a month or so.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">J. Hooker (1864 -7), pt 1, was published on I July 1864 (TL2). See J. Hooker to M, 19 September 1864.</p>
               </note> I hope I have not omitted any species that you have described. I have hunted through a vast number of Transactions &amp; Journals to obtain all I can.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am glad you were pleased with the notice of the Flora Australiensis in the Natural History Review, we are doing all we can to make it a first-class scientific periodical<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Hooker, 24 January 1864 (in this edition as 64-01-24a). The review was included in a general discussion of the Colonial Floras project, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Natural History Review</seg>, vol 3, 1863, pp 497- 507. (For the failure of the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Review</seg> in 1865, see DeArce (2012).)</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My father is extremely well &amp; has just commenced a "Synopsis Filicum"<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">W. Hooker &amp; Baker (1865-8).</p>
               </note> to be completed in one volume. Bentham is plodding away daily from 10 –3 pm at the "Flora Australiensis". he is happy in being able to work daily without interruption of any kind.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Genera Plantarum<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83).</p>
               </note> goes on very slowly. I have been 3 months at <name key="Melastomaceae">Melastomaceae</name> &amp; not done 1/4 of them — they are <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">dreadfully</hi>
               </seg> messed by Naudin.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Naudin (1849-53).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Thomson is working at the Flora Indica, which I hope to join in before long.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">J. Hooker (1875-97), vol. 1, the first part of which was not issued until May 1872 but included contributions by Thomson on <name key="Anonaceae">Anonaceae</name> and other groups, in all of which the authorship was attributed to Hooker and Thomson jointly.</p>
               </note> — he is only at <name key="Anonaceae">Anonaceae</name> as yet.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever my dear Mueller</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>most sincerely yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J D Hooker</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Anonaceae">Anonaceae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Melastomaceae">Melastomaceae</name>
            </p>
